---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Latvia Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/latvia/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Lithuania for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/lithuania' },
  { title: 'Estonia for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/estonia' },
  { title: 'Poland for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/poland' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'latviaFit', header: 'Latvia Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€280-400/mo', latviaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€330-470/mo', latviaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€260-370/mo', latviaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€240-350/mo', latviaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Latvian NHS', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'N/A', monthlyFrom: 'Tax-funded', latviaFit: 'For Residents' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '€260-400', annual: '€3,120-4,800' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '€360-530', annual: '€4,320-6,360' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '€480-720', annual: '€5,760-8,640' },
  { category: 'Latvian Public Healthcare', monthly: 'Tax-funded', annual: 'Co-payments apply' },
  { category: 'Latvian Private Clinic', monthly: '€30-100', annual: '€360-1,200' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Latvia 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Latvia. Riga's Art Nouveau, Baltic beaches, affordable EU living, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Latvia"
  subheadline="Latvia offers stunning Art Nouveau architecture, Baltic Sea beaches, affordable EU living, and improving healthcare—an emerging retirement destination."
  heroImage="/images/countries/latvia-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Latvia</h2>
  <p>
    Latvia sits at the crossroads of Baltic and Nordic culture, offering Riga's architectural splendor, pristine beaches, dense forests, and affordability. EU membership provides Schengen access and improving standards. The country offers excellent value for those seeking quiet European retirement.
  </p>

  <p>
    Riga provides cultural richness with world-class Art Nouveau architecture, opera, and restaurants. Jūrmala offers seaside spa resort living. Sigulda has castle country and nature. The countryside provides extreme peace and affordability for those seeking rural European life.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Improving; private sector reliable in Riga</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Latvian; Russian common; English in cities</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> €1,200-2,200/month; affordable by EU standards</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Baltic; cold winters, mild summers</li>
      <li><strong>EU Status:</strong> Full EU member (Eurozone; uses EUR)</li>
      <li><strong>Architecture:</strong> World's finest Art Nouveau in Riga</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Latvia's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Latvia has public healthcare funded through taxes, managed by the National Health Service. Quality is adequate in Riga but more limited in rural areas. Wait times for specialists can be significant. The system has improved with EU funding but remains below Western European standards.
  </p>

  <p>
    Private healthcare is growing in Riga. Clinics like Veselības Centrs 4, Premium Medical, and ARS offer modern facilities and shorter waits. Many locals pay out-of-pocket for private care to avoid public system delays. Costs are very reasonable by European standards.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Public Healthcare Challenges</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Latvian public healthcare faces challenges—limited funding, long waits, some facilities need updating. English is limited in public hospitals. Most expats rely on private clinics for anything beyond basic care. International insurance with evacuation coverage is recommended for complex conditions.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Latvia offers straightforward options for retirees:
  </p>

  <h3>Temporary Residence (Sufficient Means)</h3>
  <p>
    For those demonstrating sufficient income (typically €1,000+/month) and health insurance. Apply at Latvian embassy, then register upon arrival. Valid 5 years, renewable.
  </p>

  <h3>Residence for Financially Independent</h3>
  <p>
    Latvia allows residence for those who can support themselves without employment. Requires proof of regular income (pension, investments), accommodation, and health insurance.
  </p>

  <h3>EU/EEA Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    Free movement applies. Register with Office of Citizenship and Migration Affairs after 90 days. Demonstrate sufficient resources and health coverage. Full access to Latvian healthcare once registered.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Latvia:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residence application:</strong> Comprehensive health insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>EU citizens:</strong> EHIC initially; register for Latvian coverage</li>
    <li><strong>After residence:</strong> Access to public healthcare with limitations</li>
    <li><strong>Private recommended:</strong> Most expats prefer private care quality</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Latvia</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is essential for residence applications and recommended for quality care. Latvian private healthcare is affordable (€30-80 consultations) for routine needs. Keep international coverage for specialists, complex care, and potential evacuation to more advanced facilities.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Latvia, these providers offer good coverage at affordable rates:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Latvia</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Good European network, evacuation included</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive Baltic pricing</li>
    <li><strong>Latvian Private:</strong> Veselības Centrs 4, ARS for local care</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage from providers that accept seniors for Latvia.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Latvia are among the EU's lowest:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> €5,000+ deductible reduces premiums</li>
    <li><strong>Pay-as-you-go routine:</strong> Latvian private care is very affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Regional exclusions:</strong> Excluding expensive regions saves money</li>
    <li><strong>Baltic bundle:</strong> Coverage for Latvia/Lithuania/Estonia together</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Retiree, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $1,800/month pension. Attracted by Riga's architecture and value.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care for visa and comprehensive coverage. Uses Veselības Centrs 4 for routine care.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~€320/month. Lives comfortably in Riga's Old Town area on remaining pension.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Couple, Both 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Post-Brexit, seeking affordable EU with character. Combined pension £2,200/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global for both. Living in Jūrmala for beach life. UK coverage for visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~€850/month combined. Excellent lifestyle on remaining pension.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Swedish EU Citizen, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Moving from Stockholm to Riga for value. Swedish pension €1,600/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> EU rights apply. Register for Latvian coverage. Add Cigna for Sweden visits. Private clinics locally.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Latvian public + Cigna (Latvia excluded) ~€260/month. Excellent value.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Latvia really that affordable?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—among EU's cheapest countries. Comfortable life in Riga costs €1,500-2,200/month. Restaurant meals €8-15. Rent in center €500-900. Outside Riga even cheaper. Quality of life is high for the cost—culture, nature, EU benefits.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about the Russian population?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        About 25% of Latvia's population is ethnically Russian, primarily in Riga and Daugavpils. Russian is widely understood. Relations between communities are generally peaceful. The 2022 Ukraine situation affected dynamics. Russian knowledge is useful but English works in tourist/expat contexts.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's special about Riga's architecture?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Riga has the world's largest concentration of Art Nouveau buildings—over 800 in one district. UNESCO World Heritage status. Stunning facades, ornate details, well-preserved. Walking the Alberta Street area is like an open-air museum. For architecture lovers, it's paradise.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How cold are Latvian winters?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Cold but manageable. Riga averages -3 to -7°C in January, occasionally dropping to -20°C. Snow is common. Days are short (7 hours daylight). Buildings are well-heated. Coastal areas slightly milder. Summer is pleasant (18-22°C) with long days (18+ hours).
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that specialize in senior expat coverage for Latvia.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Latvian authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
